com.hazelcast.internal.networking

Class ChannelHandler<H extends ChannelHandler,S,D>

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.hazelcast.internal.networking.ChannelHandler<H,S,D>
  • Type Parameters:
    S - the type of the source. E.g. a ByteBuffer or a Supplier.
    D - the type of the destination. E.g. a ByteBuffer or a Consumer.
    Direct Known Subclasses:
    InboundHandler, OutboundHandler

    public abstract class ChannelHandler<H extends ChannelHandler,S,D>
extends Object
    ChannelHandler is either responsible for processing inbound or outbound data. ChannelHandlers are not expected to be thread-safe.

      • interceptError

        public void interceptError(Throwable error)
                    throws Throwable
        Intercepts an error that is thrown while processing the inbound or outbound pipeline. The default implementation doesn't do anything and the original Throwable is send to the ChannelErrorHandler. However in some cases like with TLS a more informative exception needs to be thrown. To prevent loosing stacktraces, it is best to include the original Throwable as cause in the new Throwable. This method will only be called from the thread owning the pipeline this handler is part of. No modifications should be done to the pipeline and no attempts should be made to 'repair' the channel. When a Throwable is thrown, it is the end of the channel.
        Parameters:
        error - the Throwable thrown while processing the pipeline.
        Throws:
        Throwable - the new Throwable

      • requestClose

        public void requestClose()
                  throws Exception
        Asks handler to trigger the closing process. Only has meaning currently for TLS. Probably this method will be replaced by some kind of general purpose event handler. An event can be thrown in the pipeline and will be pushed through each handler and it is up to the handler to respond (or not). SO we could have a close event, but also other events like handlers sending messages to each other which requires custom exchange logic currently.
        Throws:
        Exception
